# Reflection

## What I Learned

Refactoring improves the quality of code without changing its functionality. Reducing duplication, improving structure, and increasing modularity make software easier to maintain and extend over time.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

In a production environment, I would refactor incrementally while maintaining a comprehensive suite of automated tests. This ensures that structural improvements do not introduce regressions and allows the codebase to evolve safely.

